<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Sunpak service</p>
    <h2>Oldest continuously-operating US patio heater manufacturer. Gas-only specialty. Restaurant industry standard since 1957.</h2>

    <p>Sunpak (Calcana Industries, Houston Texas) has been continuously manufacturing gas patio heaters since 1957, making it the oldest US patio heater brand still in operation. Restaurants used Sunpak gas heaters before the modern electric outdoor heating industry existed. Long-running gas-only specialty means deep parts catalog stability: we service Sunpak units from the 1990s and even late-1980s installations with OEM parts still available through authorized US distribution.</p>

    <p>Common LA installations: restaurant patios across the metro (especially older establishments), residential covered patios, retail outdoor seating, hotel pool deck areas. Less prominent in luxury residential than Bromic but more prevalent in restaurant and traditional residential applications.</p>

    <p>We service the full Sunpak lineup across LA County, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. <strong>Black series</strong> (entry residential, 25,000 BTU). <strong>S25</strong> (25,000 BTU with stainless or champagne housing). <strong>S34</strong> (mid-tier 34,000 BTU). <strong>TSH (Two-Stage Heat)</strong> (premium with high/low burner switching). Natural gas and propane variants on all models.</p>

    <p>$120 outdoor diagnostic, waived with repair. <strong>BHGS #A49573</strong>. <strong>EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410</strong>. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. Parent: <a href="/outdoor/patio-heater-repair/">patio heater repair</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Lineup and what fails</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Sunpak series and common service items.</h2>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Black series, S25, S34, TSH</h3>
    <p>All four lines share core internal architecture (burner head, gas valve, thermocouple, pilot system). Differentiators are BTU output (25K, 34K, two-stage), housing material (basic black, stainless, champagne), and burner control (single-stage on Black/S25/S34, two-stage on TSH). Service approach is largely the same across all four; pricing varies modestly with housing/components.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Common service items by frequency</h3>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Thermocouple replacement (year 4-7, most common Sunpak failure).</strong> $220-340. We carry common Sunpak thermocouples on the truck.</li>
      <li><strong>Pilot light issues</strong> (often paired with thermocouple): pilot orifice cleaning, sometimes pilot tube replacement. Resolves with thermocouple service in most cases.</li>
      <li><strong>Gas valve diaphragm degradation (year 7-10)</strong>: $480-680 valve replacement, or $200-340 seal-kit rebuild on rebuildable variants.</li>
      <li><strong>Ignition spark module (electronic ignition variants, year 6-9)</strong>: $260-440.</li>
      <li><strong>Burner head corrosion (coastal LA, year 6+)</strong>: $260-440 burner head, or $440-680 full burner assembly.</li>
      <li><strong>Two-stage burner switch (TSH series, year 5-8)</strong>: $200-340 switch.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
