      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>West Hollywood restaurant patio, Sunpak S34 (commercial), 6 years old</h3>
        <p>Pilot wouldn't stay lit. Diagnosed: thermocouple weakened from continuous-cycle commercial duty (year 6 commercial-equivalent for residential year 4-7 timing). Replaced thermocouple, cleaned pilot orifice. Total: $120 plus $260 thermocouple plus $80 pilot service = $460.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Pacific Palisades residential covered patio, Sunpak S25 stainless, 9 years old</h3>
        <p>Slow ignition response and yellow flames at burner. Diagnosed: gas valve diaphragm degradation, paired with pilot orifice partial blockage. Replaced gas valve, cleaned pilot orifice. Total: $120 plus $580 gas valve plus $80 pilot service = $780.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Manhattan Beach beach-area patio, Sunpak Black series, 7 years old</h3>
        <p>Burner head significant corrosion from coastal marine layer exposure. Replaced full burner assembly (head plus venturi). Total: $120 plus $540 burner assembly plus $200 install = $860.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Pasadena residential, Sunpak TSH 1995-vintage installation</h3>
        <p>Year 30 unit (yes, 30 years old). Thermocouple plus two-stage switch plus pilot orifice cleaning. Multi-component preventive service rather than waiting for next failure. Total: $120 plus $280 thermocouple plus $260 switch plus $80 pilot = $740. Owner happy to keep an old unit running with cumulative service.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

